						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab set up in front of the Kallēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Gōvinda (III)—(Undated).</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged inscription referring itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Prabhūtavarsha,</hi> seems to record a gift of land. Since it is badly effaced and the details are lost, it is difficult to identify <hi rend="bold">Prabhūtavarsha</hi> of the record. On grounds of palaeography, however, it may be ascribed to <hi rend="bold">Gōvinda III.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
